<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                    <head>No. 427.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Manning</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-12-16"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 16,
                            1886</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 29.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 25, of the 30th
                        ultimo, touching the Mexican law as to foreigners, and have to approve your
                        note to Mr. Mariscal, of that date, relative, to the position of this
                        Government respecting the doctrine of involuntary change of allegiance as
                        embodied in Article I, Chapter V, of the Mexican law in question.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard</hi>.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>